<!-- Problem Section -->
<section class="section section-problem" id="problem">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="problem-content reveal">
            <h2>What Looked Like 'A Plan' Was Really Just A Portfolio</h2>
            
            <div class="problem-story">
                <p class="story-intro">My dad, Len, passed away suddenly at 49 while I was serving a mission for my church. In one moment, everything changed for our family.</p>
                
                <p>Dad was a custom home builder who carried all the financial leadership in our home—taxes, business decisions, insurance, income strategy. My mom, Susie, trusted him completely. They worked as a team, but like so many couples, one person held most of the financial details in their head.</p>
                
                <p>When he passed, my mom was left to untangle legal and financial complexity while grieving the loss of her husband. Contractors came saying, "Susie, if we can settle this now, there won't be any need for court." She didn't know what was legitimate and what wasn't.</p>
                
                <div class="story-highlight">
                    <p><strong>Banker boxes started showing up on my mom's floor.</strong> Statements, contracts, tax records, legal paperwork. The more I dug in, the more I saw a painful truth:</p>
                    <blockquote>"What looked like 'a plan' from the outside was really a portfolio."</blockquote>
                </div>
                
                <p>At the exact moment she needed clarity most, she got complexity. She was only 47, widowed too soon, suddenly responsible for everything.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
